headline: Wells Fargo, UBS Reel In Wealth Management Teams That Managed $1.4 Billion
summary: Wells Fargo  Advisors and  UBS  have each notched significant recruiting wins, luring seasoned advisory teams away from rivals.  The moves are the latest reminder that competition for top talent remains fierce within the wealth management industry as advisors routinely hop from one firm to another.  Wells Fargo says that the Berlin Hales Taraba Legacy Wealth Management Group, based in Newport Beach, Calif., has joined the firm from Merrill Lynch, where it managed more than $800 million.

headline: How Recent Analyst Shifts Are Rewriting The Story For Clorox (CLX)
summary: Clorox’s latest price target work reflects a slightly more cautious base case, with fair value trimmed from about US$122.41 to US$119.76 as analysts balance mixed views on volume, pricing, and earnings quality. The discount rate and long term revenue growth assumptions are essentially steady, but modestly softer expectations for the top line and earnings power have been enough to nudge the fair value estimate lower rather than higher. If you are following the stock, it is worth staying tuned...
